cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with computer vision and image processing, specifically semantic instance segmentation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training a fully convolutional network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of clustering to convey spatial extent and depth ordering suggests the involvement of unsupervised learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with object detection and localization, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
